commit.message: Use github actions for automatic tests.

Bump major version to drop Python2 support.

If any project still needs a Python2 compatible yapsy,
they must add the <2 constraints in their yapsy requirements.

The other main breaking change here is to drop the compat.py file
and its global variables.
Also ignore files generated by direnv.
Simplify implementation based on the PR comments

Remove Deprecated API's

* Replaced packaging.version instead of distutils.version
* Replaced imp module to importlib

**Note:** Probably Deprecates Python 2.7 supports, and maybe some initial versions of Python 3.x.

Signed-off-by: Ameya Vikram Singh <ameya.v.singh@gmail.com>
Added tag release_Yapsy-1.12.2 for changeset 851e4edcf10e
Add config file and badge for readthedocs

contributors' list :(
